UNITED AIR LINES
55 Million Miles Flying
UNITED AIR LINES serves directly forty-four cities
in twenty states and offers air and air-rail connec-
tions to scores of other points. (see map). Its lines, in
addition to the mid-continent route linking the Atlantic
and the Pacific seaboards, connect the Great Lakes area
to the Southwest, the Pacific Northwest to the Rocky
Mountain region and provide the only through service
on the Pacific Coast. United Air Lines has in excess of
55 million miles flying experience, of which more than
25 million miles have been flown at night. This year the
various divisions of United Air Lines will fly approxi-
mately 16,000,000 miles with passengers, mail and
press. Nearly half of this mileage will be flown at night
over government lighted airways.

Experience
United Air Lines has direct or connecting service to
137 cities. United Air Lines will gladly submit without
charge complete air or air-rail itineraries for any business
trip over the best and quickest routes between cities on
the North American continent. Traffic representatives
of this company are available for personal counsel with
executives and traffic managers of corporations in plan-
ning time and money-saving air or air-rail schedules.
Write our nearest traffic office or General Traffic
Offices, United Air Lines, Box 00, Chicago, stating in
order the cities you want to visit and the time to be
spent in each.
Or Tickets and Reservations may be
secured at all Western Union and Postal Telegraph
offices, principal hotels and travel bureaus.
